CSS- Cascading Style Sheets

CSS Rules
1. Selector
2.declaration block{}

p(selector)
{
    property : values;
    color : blue;
    font-size : 16px;
}

Selectors:

1.Universal selector(*) targets all elements
*{
    .....style goes here
}

2.Element Selector -target specific elements

h1,form,p
{
    ......style goes here
}

3.Class Selector-target elements with a specific class attribute(.)
<h3 class="highlight">Title</h3>
<p class="highlight">Test Paragraph</p>

.hightlight
{
    color : red;
}

4.ID Selector -targets one specific ::-webkit-progress-inner-element
<table id="tbl_one"></table>
#tbl_one 
{
......style
}

5.Group selectors -related or not target group 

h1,h2,h3,h4 ,p
{
......style
}

6.Descendant selector - targets elements inside another element
div(container:) 
p
{

}
padding - space outside an elements border
margin  - space inside an elements border